<div class="story">
<p>Corolla Light is an amenity rich community at the north end of the beach just before you get to the Village of Corolla with a very active home owners association. The <a href="http://www.corollalightresort.com" title="Corolla Light HOA">Corolla Light HOA</a> maintains the private roads plus the varied amenities which include   a Children's playground,   The Oceanfront Grille at Corolla Light, Training pool (heated!),  Lighted full court and half court basketball courts, Four lighted shuffleboard courts, Lighted volleyball court, Baby pool, Poolside gazebo snack bar,  Five lighted oceanfront walkways and gazebos and a Gift Shop, all at the oceanfront complex and     on the sound side, you will find a Sports Center with 2 indoor clay tennis courts, a Racquetball court, Walleyball court, Full size locker rooms with showers and sauna, a Fitness/cardio room with: 7 Startrac Treadmills, 3 Startrac Ellipticals, 1 Startrac Stepper, 1 Startrac Total Body Trainer, 3 Startrac Recumbent Bikes, 2 Startrac Upright Bikes, Weight room with free weights, Cybex Circuit Weights, and an Atlantis Multi-  Station, 25 yard indoor heated pool with 3 lap lanes, 12 person spa, Aerobics room, Pro shop with rental equipment, 2 ping pong tables, Free wi-fi lounge area with wireless printer. Plus, other   Soundside Amenities include a Swimming pool, Baby pool, Soundfront pier and gazebo, a Self-guided discovery trail, an Ecology walkway, a Nature trail and a Fishing Pond. Plus two indoor clay courts, four outdoor clay courts, and four outdoor hard courts.
    The trolley provides free transportation throughout the resort for the owners and their  guests. 
    You can find Corolla Light just past <a href="https://www.outerbankshome.com/outer banks/real estate/corolla/whalehead.asp" title="Whalehead">Whalehead</a> as you head north on Rte 12 and just before you get to <a href="https://www.outerbankshome.com/outer banks/real estate/corolla/corolla-village.asp" title="Corolla Village">Corolla Village</a>. </p>
